## Conversation
User asked to remove RemoteHTTPTraceServer and uptake the stainless server
(weave-server-sdk on test PyPI) as default; client must never import from
weave.trace_server (lint-enforced), prefer weave_server_sdk types over tsi,
ideally drop TraceServerInterface from the client; deliver a stack of PRs each
green and minimal. This commit is PR1 of the planned 6-PR stack (see
.context/sdk-uptake-plan.md): adopt the SDK + rewrite the stainless binding at
parity, interface still tsi-typed. Codex consult (thread
019eb506-341c-7d72-86e5-fcb41344e597) reshaped the stack: shared-leaf moves
land BEFORE the seam retype; retype+client-migration is one PR; no
lenient-coercion intermediate state.

