## Errors & Mistakes
- First `uv lock` failed with a bogus crewai/dspy conflict: I had inserted
  [tool.uv.sources]/[[tool.uv.index]] in the MIDDLE of [tool.uv], which
  re-parented exclude-dependencies and conflicts into the index table. TOML
  table scoping; moved the new tables after all [tool.uv] keys.
- First stream impl returned stream_ctx.__enter__() and used `with response:`
  — httpx.Response is not a context manager; also PLC2801. Replaced with
  build_request + send(stream=True) + caller close().
- Old stainless tests mocked `_stainless_client` internals and imported
  APIStatusError from the old SDK; useless against 0.0.1.

## Dead Ends
- Considered teaching utils/retry + http_utils about weave_server_sdk
  exceptions (APIError family). Rejected: a response event hook that raises
  through handle_response_error BEFORE the SDK sees the status preserves the
  exact existing exception currency (httpx.HTTPStatusError), so retry
  predicates, 413 splitting, calls-complete detection, and client catch sites
  need zero changes.
- Considered SDK resource methods for the batch flush paths. Rejected: the
  processor hands pre-encoded bytes; SDK round-trip would re-parse/re-serialize.

## Hints for Future Agents
- weave-server-sdk 0.0.1 codegen bugs (all worked around with raw _request +
  comments; remove when fixed SDK ships): duplicate generated method names
  where last-def-wins — feedback.create (=batch), objects.tags (=tags list),
  objects.create_remove (=alias remove), calls.create_usage (=/calls/usage),
  annotation_queues.query (=items query); files.create() and otel.export()
  lost their bodies. EndedCallSchemaForInsert lacks started_at (extra=allow
  saves us at runtime). TraceStatus is a Literal, not an Enum (saved_view's
  .SUCCESS will need care in PR5). No Feedback row model, no
  CompletedCallSchemaForInsert, no CallsQueryRes, no EnsureProjectExistsRes.
- Endpoints with include_in_schema=False on the server (core repo
  services/weave-trace/src/trace_server.py) are DELIBERATELY absent from the
  SDK: completions, project/stats, ttl_settings, v2 calls/complete + eager v2
  call start/end. Raw paths are by-design, not a workaround.
- /files/stats does not exist on the server; only /files/query_stats does.
  RemoteHTTPTraceServer.files_stats has been silently broken. The SDK route is
  correct; behavior intentionally fixed here.
- The response event hook MUST response.read() before inspecting error bodies
  (hooks fire before the body is read; required for streamed error responses).
- conftest server fixture relies on _send_batch_to_server.__wrapped__
  (with_retry exposes it) and on the method NAME _send_batch_to_server.
- Shared bindings tests call server._flush_calls(batch) directly, so they pass
  regardless of use_calls_complete default (True).
- Core-repo mirror CI (bot/weave-mirror/*) may fail to install weave now: the
  required dep only resolves from test PyPI. If that bites, core needs
  PIP_EXTRA_INDEX_URL=https://test.pypi.org/simple/ or equivalent. User
  explicitly approved temporary test-PyPI usage.

## Codebase Discoveries
- noxfile shards run `uv sync --frozen`, so the lockfile's test-PyPI URL pin
  flows into every CI shard with no workflow changes.
- weave/utils/http_requests builds pooled httpx clients keyed on
  (ssl_verify, http_timeout) read per call; the new binding reads them once at
  construction (set_auth mutates client auth in place rather than rebuilding).
- use_calls_complete defaults to True (settings.py:255) — calls_complete is
  the production batching mode and HAD to be ported to the stainless binding.

